SUMMARY:State of AI - AI First or Obsolete
DESCRIPTION:Modern Web (Triangle)\n​Most organizations are still treatin
 g AI like an add-on\, layering it onto workflows that were never designed 
 for it. The result is not transformation\, it is marginal improvement dres
 sed up as innovation. If your process looks the same after introducing AI\
 , you are not ahead. You are just faster at doing the wrong things.\n​\n
 The real shift is AI-first\, rebuilding how work gets done from the ground
  up. From collapsing cycle times to redefining software development and de
 cision-making\, this is where real advantage is created. We will break dow
 n what this looks like in practice and what it takes to get there at the S
 tate of AI event.\n\nFeaturing a panel of experts from This Dot Labs:\n[Tr
 acy Lee](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tracyslee/)\, CEO\n[Elliott Fouts](ht
 tps://www.linkedin.com/in/elliott-fouts/)\, CTO\n[Brandon Mathis](https://
 www.linkedin.com/in/mathisbrandon/)\, Engineering Lead\n[Coston Perkins](h
 ttps://www.linkedin.com/in/costonperkins/)\, Engineering Lead\n[Jonathan F
 ontanez](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jonathan-fontanez-27715428/)\, AI Eng
 ineering Lead\n\n[Watch our most recent State of AI event here.](https://w
 ww.youtube.com/watch?v=sVIZjFhqE7M)
